    "answers": [{
        "owner": {
            "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/wpk6X.jpg?s=256",
            "account_id": 1961640,
            "user_type": "registered",
            "user_id": 1763035,
            "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1763035/andy-brown",
            "reputation": 13417,
            "display_name": "Andy Brown",
            "accept_rate": 56
        },
        "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
        "score": 2,
        "is_accepted": true,
        "last_activity_date": 1539944137,
        "creation_date": 1539944137,
        "body": "<p>This is likely to be a compatibility failure with the new PSS algorithms in TLS 1.3. You can read a good explanation for the reasoning behind the introduction of PSS <a href=\"https://crypto.stackexchange.com/a/58708\">here<\/a>.<\/p>\n\n<p>Until it's fixed you can prevent your server from negotiating TLS 1.3 by editing <code>lib/security/java.security<\/code> and adding TLSv1.3 to the <code>jdk.tls.disabledAlgorithms<\/code> property.<\/p>\n",
        "answer_id": 52890358,
        "question_id": 52830481
    }],
